AGI - US President, Donald Trump and his main advisers gathered in the Oval Studio after the fierce diverb with Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky, which took place yesterday in favor of cameras at the White House, decided that Kiev leader had to leave.> But the differences, reveals the well-informed Axios site, were born before entering the Oval Studio. After the clamorous diverb, "the Kiev delegation waited in another room for about an hour, hoping to sign the agreement on minerals that had prompted Zelensky to visit Washington," reports Axios.
Trump and Zelensky still had plans to have lunch and hold a joint press conference, but then Secretary of State Marco Rubio and National Security Counselor Mike Waltz "goed out of the Oval Studio, approached Zelensky and told him to leave", told Axios a senior White House official.
A small, but not insignificant factor that irritated Trump was the fact that Zelensky did not wear a dress, but his now traditional uniform, > told Axios two sources of direct knowledge of the facts. Trump's advisers said on several occasions to the Zelensky team that it would be more respectful by the Ukrainian president to abandon his military-style clothing when he would go to the White House. Zelensky instead presented himself wearing a more formal black dress, decorated with the national symbol of Ukraine, but without jacket and tie. "Today it's all dressed up," Trump commented, holding hands on Zelensky at the West Wing entrance.
